==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Copepoda
<hw>Co*pep"o*da</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL., from
Gr. <?/ an oar + <ets>-poda</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>An
order of Entomostraca, including many minute Crustacea, both fresh-water
and marine.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ They have a distinct carapace. The eggs are carried in a
pair of external pouches. Some are parasites of fishes.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Copernican</ent>⟦br⟧
